HEADWORD: Prophylaxis
<hw>Proph`y*lax"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Prophylactic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The art of
preserving from, or of preventing, disease; the observance of the rules
necessary for the preservation of health; preservative or preventive
treatment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

